Model Evaluation¶

Evaluating the models using metrics.

In [46]:
def evaluate_model(model_name, y_true, y_pred):
    mse = mean_squared_error(y_true, y_pred)
    r2 = r2_score(y_true, y_pred)
    print(f'{model_name} - MSE: {mse:.2f}, R2: {r2:.2f}')

evaluate_model('Linear Regression', y_test, lr_pred)
evaluate_model('Decision Tree Regressor', y_test, dt_pred)
evaluate_model('Random Forest Regressor', y_test, rf_pred)
evaluate_model('Bagging Regressor', y_test, bag_pred)
evaluate_model('Gradient Boosting Regressor', y_test, gb_pred)

Linear Regression - MSE: 270.64, R2: 0.00
Decision Tree Regressor - MSE: 42.78, R2: 0.84
Random Forest Regressor - MSE: 20.64, R2: 0.92
Bagging Regressor - MSE: 25.04, R2: 0.91
Gradient Boosting Regressor - MSE: 230.42, R2: 0.15

Hyperparameter Turning¶

Tuning models to improve performance

In [47]:
# Hyperparameter tuning for Random Forest
rf_params = {'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200], 'max_depth': [None, 10, 20, 30]}
rf_grid = GridSearchCV(rf_model, rf_params, cv=3, scoring='r2')
rf_grid.fit(X_train, y_train)
best_rf = rf_grid.best_estimator_
In [48]:
# Hyperparameter tuning for Gradient Boosting
gb_params = {'n_estimators': [50, 100, 200], 'learning_rate': [0.01, 0.1, 0.2]}
gb_grid = GridSearchCV(gb_model, gb_params, cv=3, scoring='r2')
gb_grid.fit(X_train, y_train)
best_gb = gb_grid.best_estimator_
In [49]:
# Evaluate tuned models
best_rf_pred = best_rf.predict(X_test)
best_gb_pred = best_gb.predict(X_test)

evaluate_model('Tuned Random Forest Regressor', y_test, best_rf_pred)
evaluate_model('Tuned Gradient Boosting Regressor', y_test, best_gb_pred)

Tuned Random Forest Regressor - MSE: 20.51, R2: 0.92
Tuned Gradient Boosting Regressor - MSE: 177.48, R2: 0.35
